	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>With my RL job, I'm on-call one day every two weeks.  On that day, if I'm playing, and I think it's likely I will be called (ie, early enough in the day that calls may come in) I don't join a LDoN.  If I think it's unlikely I will be called, I may try to get a group, but will explain to the group that, due to my job, I may be called away; and if it's not acceptable to ALL the members of the group, I will bow out.<br />
<br />
If the group was hanging around waiting for a sixth, and a raid was called, I would raid.  Once that Adv is accepted, I've a contract with my fellow Adv-mates to finish it.<br />
<br />
For me, at least:<br />
RL Family > RL job > LDoN Active Adv > Guild > XP Group > LDoN Inactive Adv</p>
	
	
	
