<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Tetrass</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Aug 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>There are two things about this thread that absolutely astound me.  <br />
<br />
The first is the number of people who just patently say things like 'guild > all/xp/ldon/pickup group/whatever' without any consideration of the factors surrounding the situation.  Based on the original post, I would most likely have stayed in the LDoN.  When the situation was clarified to explain that 5 of the 6 people in the group had a reason to leave the LDoN I almost changed my mind, right up until the part where they even went so far as to enter the LDoN <i>after</i> the raid started to form and then stayed for 45 min.  If they had just not zoned in then there would be no loss on the record and a very limited amount of time wasted.  It really sounds like a bunch of people who were trying to have their cake and eat it too, ie. they thought they could finish the LDoN a lot faster than they could.<br />
<br />
The second thing about this thread that disturbs me is the hypocrisy.  Many of the people saying they would leave the LDoN no question are those same folks who rain fire and brimstone down on others from an assumed position of moral superiority.  I've watched people get criticized and derided here over issues like looting some almost expired trash mob that they didn't kill, getting PL'd, buying MQs for quests,  and a whole host of other minor issues.  Somehow though, those same 'morally superior' people are now advocating behavior far more reprehensible than any of the things they rail against.<br />
<br />
I am generally a pretty content player most of the time.  I don't get worked up over class issues enough to want to quit over it, or really just about anything else.  What does make me consider quitting more than anything though is when I start to dwell on the human garbage I am voluntarily surrounding myself with when I log on.  I'm not saying that it's everyone, or even most or even a lot of players, but the thought that I might actually end up grouped with people who are so thoughtlessly hypocritical depresses me.<br />
<br />
<b> Let me make it real simple:  if you think there's a chance you will have to leave an LDoN then you shouldn't be there.  If that means you only do them with all guild groups, then so be it.  If that means you only do them late at night when the raiding is done, then so be it.  If that means you NEVER do an LDoN, then so be it.  If you mean what you say when you say things like 'guild over (whatever)' then put your money where your damn mouth is and don't expect the rest of the world to compensate for your lack of judgement.</b></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22240">Hunter Tetrass</a><br />
Forest Stalker(65)<br />
<br />
<br />
Innoruuk Server</div>
	
	
