	<p>woohoo ... a post I started made it to two pages :P<br />
<br />
Let me point out that I agree wasting peoples time is bad.  I felt crummy about leaving the group in an LDoN adventure we were struggling to pass.  But I still don't get why LDoN time >> than any other time?  Granted I only have 1000 total ldon points so I don't understand their importance or lure I guess.  <br />
<br />
I am a pretty casual gamer .. an hour or two for three maybe four nights a week.  When I spend an hour out of my two hour group exp grind waiting to replace members who zip in and out of the group thats no big deal but waste an LDoN'ers time and thats a sin?<br />
<br />
Roughly<br />
1 hour BoT = 1AA<br />
1 hour ldon = 50%AA and 50 adventure points.<br />
<br />
to me 1 hour = 1 hour.  If you waste an hour in a pick up exp group or you waste an hour ditching an LDoN they are equally bad.<br />
<br />
But I think the lesson to me from this is clear .. stay the hell away from LDoN adventures ... LDoNers take this stuff way more seriously than I do :P.</p>
	
	
	
