<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>SokkoMatic</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Member<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2003<br />
	Location: Not lost... exploring
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I would not leave an LDoN for any in game reason. I start it, I finish it. To the end. Failure, LD's, wipes, idiocy... I stick it out.<br />
<br />
I completely understand if someone else takes off for any reason... hey, thats their perogative. But be sure, I take note of what Guild they are in and their name. If it happens more than once, you will be on my do not group with list.<br />
<br />
If you are going to be committed to raiding, be committed. But do the rest of us a favor and let us know <i>before</i> we group with you. Or dont group outside your Guild. Do something else if not raiding. Tradeskill, solo, farm...<br />
<br />
Just remember, reputation is reputation... You may be a star to your Guild, but if everyone else thinks your an asshat... you are an asshat. Groups will become very difficult to find outside of those in your Guild.<br />
<br />
If you do not care... that is fine. But dont wonder why folks get mad that you wasted their time.</p>
	
	
	
