	<p>i stand by my statement of guild > all<br />
<br />
like i said my guild is ALLWAYS there for me, random people that i see in a  pickup group 1 time a month arnt. Does it suck for them? sure it does. but ide rather be on their "do not group list" than be deguilded and be on my guilds "do not group list" especially since 95% of my groups are guild groups.<br />
<br />
    Anytime you do pickup groups this is the risk you run. peopel leave, people ld, people decide its taking to long and gate out, crap happens. If i was ina  group and had peopel leave for raids, which HAS happened to me a few times, i never hold it against them, you can ldon mornign noon or night, guild raids are usually only when you have enough peopel on and if u dont move to that target within 30 minutes another guild gets it. i dont hold peopel leaving groups agaisnt them for raids as i know ide do the same thing.<br />
<br />
    I took the time to look at almost everyone magelo in this entire thread, i notice that the majority of people who say they would never leave are not very well equiped cause they arnt in raid guilds, and then all the people who are well equiped are all the raiders who all say they would leave without thinking twice. I think theres some reasons for this. The hardcore raiders all will leave in a flash becuase they have put so much time and effort into their guilds that a ldon means nothing to them other than augs. And then the other peopel who are the ones who arnt in raiding guilds basically ldon is their raiding guild, they feel the same way about ldon as the others feal about their guilds. the think its rediculous and rude for you to leave a ldon, just as you feel the same way about not leaving the ldon<br />
<br />
   I know servers are all diffrent, but i think its safe to say that if you do a pickup group on Terris THule and theres a  valon, ctv, nocturnal, xenosis,DM, SU, DT name above their head you take the chance that theres a good possibility they might be called to a raid and are going to leave you. IMo pickup groups are allways at your own risk, dont want the risk? then group with friends or guildmates</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Huntress Shooten<br />
65 Forest Stalker <br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=256318" target="_blank">My Crap</a></div>
	
	
