	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />As an officer, I'd look rather dimly on some guildie bailing out of a LDoN to join a guild effort - it normally means (s)he couldn't manage his time properly, and it will reflect badly on the guild's image.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>The correct response would be to look dimly on a member who was irresponsible enough to enter an LDON when a raid was likely, or to enter in to one in which leaving would be disruptive.<br />
