<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Riudi Oaknoggin</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Senior Member<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2000<br />
	Location: Wanderer
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Hey I have no problem with Guild>all.<br />
<br />
What I have a problem with is people who are not being responsible enough to figure out if a raid is coming or not.  When people in our guild log on, the first thing that comes out is usually, "what are we doing today?"  They want to know if they have <b>time</b> enough to do an LDoN or not.  In the vast majority of cases, our guild leadership knows what is going to spawn and where, so that we don't have this problem.<br />
<br />
If you log on and go, "Ok, who want's to do a quick LDoN?", and you get a reply like "We're checking raid targets!", then your best bet is to go do exp.  <br />
<br />
My guild is Time enabled.  We've been at the top end of the game for 2 years.  Professionalism requires us to be responsible enough to get these things done right, which means fulfilling responsiblities.<br />
<br />
Personal note:  I don't do pickup LDoN's.  I never have.  All my adventures have been guild groups.  That is, and will continue to be the best way to do an LDoN.  With people you know and trust.</p>
	
	
	
