<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Mortok</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Bow to my helm!<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Oct 2000<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>The question I would like answered is when did your time become more important than mine?<br />
<br />
This thread came up shortly after LDoN was released and got roughly the same responses (which I would have hoped would have changed over time).  It simply is embarrassing that some people would leave a LDoN group they started knowing that they have a chance to be called away to a raid.  Simple solution for all the high and mighty raiding guild people is to not do LDoN groups unless it is a "free day" in guild.  Don't waste my time if you are "commited" to your guild.  DON'T BE GREEDY.<br />
<br />
If I was the 6th person in Legran's group I would have been rightfully pissed off.  What it really comes down to is how greedy do you plan on being knowing that you have the possibility to raid.  Most thoughtful and respectful people will simply not do LDoN groups (on raiding days) because they full on know that they will have wasted someone elses time yet there are still quite a few of you that could care less about other people and have made the decision to be greedy.  Greedy because you are living on the edge and there really is no downside for you... but for me its wasted time.<br />
<br />
Do this each time you decide to do a LDoN group.  Simply make a hotkey that says this:<br />
<br />
"/g My guild is raiding today and there is a slight chance that I will be called away.  Due to this I realize that this may cause the group to fail the adventure.  I would like to inform you now and if you want to kick me out of group I fully understand."<br />
<br />
This would atleast give the other group members the full information and could then make an informed decision on whether or not to keep you in because you are a liability.  If they keep you in then they are assuming the risks of having you in.  <br />
<br />
Here is where it gets funny.  How many of these people who claim "guild >> all" would be willing to make a hotkey announcing this when there are 3-4 other people that could easily fill their slot?</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1466" target="_blank">Hunter Mortok Swiftarrow</a><br />
Forest Stalker - Terris Thule<br />
"Rangers lead the way!"</div>
	
	
