<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Shaolin_X</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Member<br />
	
	
	<br />
	Joined: Feb 2001<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I've run into this situation once before, and I made the choice to stay with the group until we finished. A fire raid was called and I was one of the last to get there, and likely would not have made it (I have to be piggybacked) were it not for the good graces of our CotH pig team. <br />
<br />
My mistake was to accept an invitation to an LDON adventure about 45 minutes prior to when the GL and raid officers usually log on. I was chastised by a few guildmates, and rightly so (especially considering I have to be piggybacked in, and thus delay things for other folks i.e. it's not just my time now, it involves other people). <br />
<br />
So, it is contingent upon you, particularly if you are in a higher end raiding guild, to be available and on time to drop targets (if you're online of course). With that being said, I bit the bullet and stayed behind, because were I to leave, it would inconvenience the folks who asked me to group in the first place. As much as I want to help my guild I also cannot just toss the group aside as a result of my own poor judgement call. That to me is a rather distasteful thing to do. You have to live with the consequences of your decisions.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=455393">Hunter Lonnlarcan Shadowblade</A><BR><SMALL><I>Warder, 65 Seasons<BR>Tunare's Bladesworn</I><BR><SMALL><BR>A bell tolls against the hollow sky<br />
Ravens caw...no mercy!<br />
All samurai walk the path to nothingness...<P ALIGN="LEFT"> -- Kuroi Sabato,<I> Blade of the Immortal</I></SMALL></div>
	
	
