	<p>My favorite response was this<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />I'd drop any group for a guild raid. My guild uses a DKP system, which is why.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>So what makes your guilds DKP points more important than the personal "DKP" points the other 5 in the group have to earn for  upgrades through LDON?<br />
<br />
That seems pretty selfish to me. Basically the only reason to LDON is for the armor, weapons, and augments. Which all require a lot of points.<br />
<br />
A suite of nice LDON armor si 10,444 points IIRC. Most casual gamers see LDON as their only chance at a huge upgrade to armor. Alot I know, including myself, want a full suit, plus random pieces, plus alot of augs.. that's a     ton of points.. and every LDON is working towards that effort.. So once again what makes your     ty DKP poitns more important than the points for the other 5 people's points they are working hard to get? Cause remember when you bail on LDON you are not just screwing yourself out of a few points.. you're screwing 5 other people.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
